data.title: Terrible!! Never again
data.text: So my wife went to this location the yesterday afternoon and woke up at 3 o'clock this morning having irritable tummy cramps and violently throwing up everywhere. Called the store owner or the manager don't know which one, but was not very helpful all. We  did not want our money back just wanted to let them know that either clean up better going forward or to check their supplies cuz something there made her violently sick, will never visit the subway again lousy customer service and whoever we talked to didn't even care.

data.title: Super clean
data.text: My go to place before my trips to Sequoia National Park. This location is always clean with super friendly staff. I usually get a couple of Turkey foot longs for my trip and the staff always offers me the mayo, oil and vinegar on the side.

data.title: What? Where's the anything?
data.text: Depending on which Subway you visit, the product varies. Personally, you no longer get value for the money since sandwiches are the cheapest to make for customers. I give Subway a huge thumbs down.

data.title: Huge Subway
data.text:
The largest [and clean] Subway I've ever been in.  Stopped here to get a couple of sandwiches before driving up to Sequoia Nat Park.

They provided us with mayo, oil and vinegar packets on the side so the sandwiches would not get soggy.

Can't ask for much more than that for $8 sandwiches.

Service was quick and helpful.

Food was cheap, but good.

Recommended,
